description:
&lt;h1&gt;Lead Pharmacist&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Due to the promotion of the current post holder an exciting opportunity has arisen for a motivated and enthusiastic pharmacist to lead our gastroenterology and surgical pharmacy team.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The successful applicant will be responsible for leading and developing the clinical pharmacy service to our adult surgical wards. You will also be a core member of the nutrition team providing support to adult patients in hospital and at home working closely with the lead consultant and a team of dietitians.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The role includes working closely with the Gastroenterology team and interpreting budgetary information with particular reference to compliance with formulary, NICE guidance and general clinical issues and supporting the work with CCGs specifically prescribing of high cost drugs and homecare expenditure.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You will have the opportunity to develop your leadership and educational skills by supervising band 7 and 6 rotational pharmacists and the medicines management technician who will work alongside you.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Working closely with the wider MDT will give you the chance to be closely involved with developments and innovation to take the service forward. You will be supported and guided by the senior team to ensure you reach your full potential.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PHT is a the largest non-teaching hospital Trust in England with an annual turnover of close to £550m and employing around 7,000 members of staff, providing comprehensive acute and specialist services. Our main site is the Queen Alexandra Hospital, located in Cosham, serving a population of 675,000 residents of Portsmouth and south east Hampshire. The Trust is home to the Wessex Renal and Transplant Unit (WRTS) and it holds prestigious Cancer Beacon Status for the Head and Neck Cancer Services. The Trust also hosts the largest of one of five Ministry of Defence Hospital Unit (MDHU) in England. We continue to build our reputation for innovation and excellence, consistently delivering outstanding performance, whilst developing the skills and abilities of our staff.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Portsmouth is a vibrant city and tourist destination on the south coast with convenient access to the South Downs National Park and the Isle of Wight and just 90 minutes from London Waterloo by train. Whether your passion is the outdoors, with beaches, sailing, kite-surfing, horse-riding and hiking on our doorstep, or culture, in the birthplace of Charles Dickens, with two theatres and a major concert venue in the city, Portsmouth has something for everyone. If history is your hobby, Portsmouth Historic Dockyard offers a rich exploration of Britain’s naval history, but if retail therapy is more likely to float your boat, discount designer-label shopping at Gunwharf Quays attracts shoppers from far and wide. If you like to travel and explore, Portsmouth ferries sail to the Channel Islands, France and Spain and cruise ships depart from nearby Southampton to the Mediterranean, Baltic, Carribean and Nordic seas. Southampton airport is just 20 miles away, serving destinations across the British Isles and Europe.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing Date 12/11/20&lt;/p&gt;
